As of the 2010 census, the population of the Fence Lake CDP was 42, consisting of 23 households, of which 11 were families. Females were 54.8% of the population. The racial make-up of the CDP was 26.2% [[Race and ethnicity in the United States Census|Native American]], 71.4% [[Caucasian Race|White]], and 2.4% Asian. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race was 4.8% of the population.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US3526010| archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212142922/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US3526010| url-status=dead| archive-date=February 12, 2020| title=Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics: 2010 Demographic Profile Data (DP-1): Fence Lake CDP, New Mexico| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau, American Factfinder| accessdate=October 20, 2014}}</ref>

